Working People's Organizations Celebrate February 16 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- A meeting of workers and trade union members took place at the Central Workers' Hall on Feb. 14 to celebrate the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, made a report at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers said that Kim Jong Il has wisely led the revolutionary cause of Juche for decades, performing epoch-making feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il has developed in depth the Songun idea and line, founded and consistently embodied by President Kim Il Sung, as required by the era and the developing revolution, they noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A poem devoted to his birthday "Song of Best Wishes to February" was recited at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A performance was given by the workers' art squad of the GFTUK Central Committee on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 That day a meeting of members of the Korean Democratic Women's Union for celebrating February 16 was held at the Women's Hall. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Sun Hui, chairwoman of the Central Committee of the union, in her speech said that the course of the glorious and brilliant revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Il represents a heroic epical history for the genius of revolution and construction, a peerlessly brilliant commander who has glorified the history of modern Korea as the history of great Kim Il Sung's Korea under the banner of the ever-victorious Juche idea, the Songun idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 An art performance was given at the meeting. Its performers included women who have distinguished themselves in upholding the Songun revolutionary leadership of the Workers' Party of Korea, members of the women's union who have devoted their ardent patriotism to the building of a rich and powerful country, women who have done a lot of good things for society and the collective, the mothers who brought up their sons and daughters as strong pillars of the country and officials of women's union organizations at all levels. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the functions was Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the WPK.

Iranian Ambassador Hosts Reception 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- Iranian Ambassador to the DPRK Jalaleddin Namini Mianji hosted a reception at the embassy on Feb. 14 on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 The ambassador said in a speech that Kim Jong Il served as an aide to President 
Kim Il Sung in his revolutionary work from long ago and is successfully carrying forward and accomplishing his cause after his demise. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He hoped that the bilateral relations would further expand and develop in various fields. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He supported the Korean people in their struggle for the reunification of the country and hoped for peace and security on the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly of the DPRK, speaking next, said:  We, who value the friendly and cooperative relations with Iran forged in the struggle for independence against imperialism and the U.S., will work hard to expand and develop the bilateral relations onto a new higher stage in various fields this year, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the great achievements made by the government and people of Iran in the work for the independent development of the country and its economic growth despite the moves of the U.S. to interfere in the internal affairs of Iran and isolate and stifle it, he extended support and solidarity to the Iranian government and people in their efforts to attain the right of peaceful nuclear activities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were Jong Yong Su, minister of Labor, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, and other officials concerned.

Foreigners Visit Kimjongilia Festival Venue
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- Foreign diplomatic envoys, representatives of international organizations and officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of foreign embassies here visited the venue of the 10th Kimjongilia Festival on Feb. 14.
 The guests went round immortal flowers in full bloom with deep emotion and made entries in the visitor's book. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Cuban Ambassador Ruben Perez Valdes wrote that Kimjongilia carrying the august name of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il is blooming all over the world.
 Councilor of the Romanian embassy Ioan Dedean wrote that the visit to the festival venue offered him an opportunity to know well about boundless reverence for Kim Jong Il and the might of the Korean people's unity around him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Earlier, officials in charge of cultural and friendly relations of foreign embassies visited the venue of the first national sketch festival for celebrating February 16.

Friendly Meeting for Officials of Working People's Organizations
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- Chinese Ambassador to the DPRK Wu Donghe arranged a friendly meeting for officials of working people's organizations at the embassy on Feb. 14.
 Present on invitation were Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, Kang Chang Uk, chairman of the Central Committee of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea, Pak Sun Hui, chairperson of the Central Committee of the Korean Democratic Women's Union, and other officials of working people's organizations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were officials of the Chinese embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants talked to each other about the development of exchange and cooperation between the working people's organizations of the two countries under the deep care of leader Kim Jong Il and President Hu Jintao, deepening friendship.

Film Show for Chinese Residents
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- The Pyongyang City People's Committee arranged a film show for Chinese residents in the city at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on Feb. 14 on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Present on invitation were officials of the Central Committee of the Federation of Chinese Residents in Korea including its vice-chairman and Chinese residents in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were officials of the Pyongyang City People's Committee.
 The participants saw a Korean documentary film "Grand Celebration of the 60th Anniversary of the Party Foundation in the Presence of the Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The film show was followed by a singing session of Chinese residents for celebrating the auspicious holiday of February. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers emotionally sang such songs of praise for the great persons as "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il" and "We Present Best Wishes".
 They also put on the stage colorful numbers including mixed duet "The Country I Am Defending", male chorus "Blue Sky over My Country", female solo "Songun Nilliri" and mixed singing in unison with drums beating "My Prosperous Country".

New Technology for Photographing Underground Fault Developed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- The Geological Institute under the State Academy of Sciences of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has developed a new technology for photographing underground fault.
 Pictures  of such complex topographical and geological features as Korea's which were taken with the previous photographing technique are not clear so that they could not ensure the scientific accuracy of analysis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Scientists found out the principle of concentrating the sensitivity and solved scientific and technical issues arising in its application. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new technology makes it possible to photograph even a section 200 meters deep under the ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The projects of boring and tunneling pits to survey stratum are not needed any more.
 In recent years, the survey of dam beds for power stations could be carried out in a short time with the help of the new technology. As the result, the speed of projects has been increased and the safety of structures been ensured so as to reduce state investment remarkably.

Samjiyon Schoolchildren's Palace Reconstructed on Expansion Basis
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- The Samjiyon Schoolchildren's Palace, located at the foot of Mt. Paektu in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, has been  reconstructed on an expansion basis.
 It, with a total floor space of 7,800 square meters, consists of the main building, a theater and a gymnasium. The palace has more than 120 rooms and 20 circle rooms.
 It goes well with the surrounding topographical features in formative arts. And the decorations engraved on its interior and exterior in relief and murals caters to  the aesthetic sense of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main building houses a computer room, an electronic amusement room and a library. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are murals reflecting juvenile stories told by the three generals of Mt. Paektu in the theatre with a 300-odd seating capacity. And its stage is furnished with modern lighting apparatuses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Well arranged in the gymnasium with waiting rooms are places for basketball, volleyball, table-tennis and Taekwon-Do. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Leader Kim Jong Il, while guiding the work in Samjiyon County on the spot in October Juche 91 (2002), said that as a large number of expeditionists visit there every year, the schoolchildren's palace should be rebuilt on an expansion basis along modern line and better cultural and welfare facilities provided to them. And he showed a great love and affection so that it could be reconstructed on a high level.

National Meeting Celebrates February 16
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- A national meeting to celebrate February 16 took place at the April 25 House of Culture Wednesday.
 Among those present there were Kim Yong Nam, Jo Myong Rok, Pak Pong Ju and other senior officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present there on invitation were diplomatic envoys of different countries, representatives of international organizations and members of the military attaches' corps here and other foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, alternate member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, in a report said that the birth of leader Kim Jong Il as a son of legendary guerillas at a time when the great event of the liberation of Korea that meant the ultimate victory in the anti-Japanese war was approaching was a great fortune for the nation and an auspicious event for humankind as it brought about a bright future in carving out the destiny of the Koreans and in the history of the development of the Juche revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The reporter continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il's sacred history of revolutionary leadership is great in that he applied President Kim Il Sung's revolutionary idea and exploits and built socialist Korea of Juche where the President's noble idea of achieving the independence of the popular masses has come true and reliably defended the sovereignty of the country and the nation and the destiny of the country and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il' glorious history of revolutionary activities has been a history of great succession as he has met all challenges of history, firmly defended the idea and cause of the President and steadily carried the Juche revolution to successful completion, holding high the banner of the idea of Songun, the banner of the Juche idea.
�@To consolidate the single-minded unity of the servicepersons and people around the leader as firm as an iron wall provides a basic guarantee for achieving the prosperity of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It is necessary to thoroughly establish the trait of attaching importance to the military affairs throughout the society and give top priority to the development of national defence industry as required by the line of economic construction in the Songun era and thus steadily bolster up the war deterrent for self-defence.
�@This year we should put spurs to the general march of the Songun revolution once again under the militant slogan "Make fresh leap forward in building a great prosperous powerful socialist country with the might of Songun!" and bring about a radical turn in the economic construction and in the efforts to improve the standard of the people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The reporter called for waging the vigorous patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity true to the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration to  resolutely foil all the obstructive moves of the U.S. and its allied forces and bring about a fresh turning phase in the cause of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@All the issues between the DPRK and the U.S. including the nuclear issue can never be settled as long as the U.S. invariably pursues an anachronistic hostile policy toward the DPRK, the reporter noted, warning that the army and people of the DPRK will mobilize all the potentials they have built up with the might of Songun and thus wipe out the aggressors to the last man and victoriously conclude the protracted stand-off with the U.S. should the U.S. ignite a war of aggression against it at any cost.

10th Kimjongilia Festival Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- The 10th Kimjongilia Festival was inaugurated with splendor here.
 On display at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition, the venue of the festival situated on the bank of the River Taedong, are more than 23,000 potted Kimjongilias presented by over 100 organizations including military organs, commissions and ministries of the Cabinet,  national institutions and servicepersons, working people from all walks of life, school youth and children and the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) and overseas Koreans, foreign embassies in Pyongyang and friendship and social organizations in different countries and Chinese residents in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Immortal Kimjongilias, a variety of beautiful and rare flowers and decorations in the venue presented fantastic scenery.
 An opening ceremony took place on Feb. 14. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Choe Thae Bok, Yang Hyong Sop and Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, and others. 
 Also present there were members of delegations of Chongryon including a congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan headed by Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of Chongryon, and members of other congratulatory groups of overseas Koreans staying in the socialist homeland to celebrate the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kang Nung Su, chairman of the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Committee, in his opening address said that the annual grand festival is a floral festival representing the best wishes of the servicepersons and people as they extend the greatest glory and the warmest congratulations to Kim Jong Il who has demonstrated the dignity and might of Songun Korea all over the world and a great political festival showcasing the true appearance of the Korean people firmly rallied around him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The desire of the servicepersons and the people of the DPRK to cultivate with all care Kimjongilia shining with the august name of the peerlessly great man and bring it into full bloom has grown stronger year after year and the Kimjongilia festival got more unique in its form and gained in scope as the days go by, he said.
 He called upon all the participants in the festival to widely introduce the greatness of Kim Jong Il through the cultivation propagation of the immortal flower and festival and fully demonstrate the single-minded unity of the Korean society. 
 At the end of the ceremony, its participants looked round the exhibition of the flower of the sun.

Demonstration March of Korean and Russian Military Bands
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- The Korean and Russian military bands made a demonstration march in Pyongyang on Feb. 14 to celebrate February 16.
 Participating in the march were the military band of the Korean People's Army and the central military band of the Defence Ministry of Russia on a visit to the DPRK.
 Lined up at the foot of Mansu Hill where the statue of President Kim Il Sung is standing was a march troupe consisting of the Korean and Russian military bands for celebrating February 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The march began with the two military bands' joint playing of "Song of General Kim Jong Il" and "March of Songun Victory". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The marchers started. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The KPA military band made a proud march, solemnly performing song "Long Live Generalissimo Kim Il Sung", "The General Is the Son of Guerrillas" and "No Motherland without You". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The central military band of the Defence Ministry of Russia marched full of vigor, playing songs "Victory" and "March of Russia" which represent the militant and optimistic life of the Russian army and people who wiped out fascism.
 Valerii Khalilov, chief of the Military Orchestra Service and its chief conductor of the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation, praised Kim Jong Il for paying a deep concern to the art of military music, noting that he came to know well about the Songun politics through his several visits to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The march troupe entered Kim Il Sung Square through Changjon crossroads.
 The march troupe was welcomed at the square by Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov and embassy officials together with working people in the city.
 The march ended with the playing of wind music "Please Receive Our Salute".

U.S. Invariable Attempt at Preemptive Nuclear Attack Assailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- The U.S. Bush administration in a "defense review report" published by the Defense Department shortly ago singled out the military operation against "terrorist organizations and rogue states" as an important military strategic task and disclosed the plan to drastically bolster up special military force to this end.
  This once again clearly proves the bellicose nature of the U.S. as a major harasser of global peace and stability, observes Minju Joson Wednesday in a signed commentary.
  It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The true aim sought by the U.S. in its loud-mouthed military operation against "rogue states" is to put into practice its attempt at a preemptive nuclear attack on the anti-imperialist independent countries at any cost and realize its ambition to hold world hegemony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. ambition to dominate the world through adventurous preemptive nuclear attacks is a pipe dream. The U.S. nuke-is-all-powerful theory will never work on any part of the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those fond of playing with fire are bound to perish in the flames kindled by themselves, the commentary observes, urging the Bush administration not to forget the lesson taught by history but immediately drop its anachronistic policy.

Kim Jong Il Enjoys Performance Given by Russian Military Band
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 15 (KCNA) -- Supreme Commander of the Korean People's Army Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, Wednesday enjoyed a performance given by the central military band of the Defence Ministry of Russia on a visit to the DPRK.
 He was greeted at the theatre by Valerii Khalilov, chief of the Military Orchestral Service and its chief conductor of the Armed Forces of the Russian Federation, and Andrei Karlov, Russian ambassador to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il warmly welcomed the DPRK visit of the military band and had a cordial conversation with the Russian guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When he appeared in the auditorium, the entire audience enthusiastically welcomed him with a stormy applause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the Russian central military band offered him the best wishes, presenting him with bouquets that represented their deepest reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the audience were Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Pak Pong Ju, Chief of the KPA General Staff Kim Yong Chun who is member of the NDC of the DPRK, Minister of the People's Armed Forces Kim Il Chol who is member of the NDC of the DPRK, and Choe Thae Bok and Kim Ki Nam, secretaries of the Central Committee of the WPK, Vice-President of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly Yang Hyong Sop, First Vice-Minister of Foreign Affairs Kang Sok Ju and leading cadres of the Party and the army, senior officials of ministries and national institutions and officials in the fields of literature and arts and media and KPA servicepersons.
 Also among the audience were the Russian ambassador and staff members of the Russian embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Artistes of the Russian central military band put on the stage piano concerto "The first movement of No. 2 Piano Concerto composed by Rakhmaninov", female soprano "Oriole", wind music "March of Songun Victory", wind music for trumpet solo "Venice Carnival", bass solo "Long Journey", sopilka solo "Vatra", accordion solo "Carrousel", wind music for xylophone solo "Russian Mosaic", female solo of folk song "Saturday", wind music waltz "Friendship" and other colorful numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers truthfully represented the Russian people's warm love of the country, their optimistic life and national custom in high artistry. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance ended with wind music "Song of General Kim Jong Il".
 The performance was highly acclaimed by the audience as it was pervaded with the warm feelings of the DPRK-Russia friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il sent a floral basket to the Russian artistes, congratulating them on their successful performance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a photo session with the artistes of the Russian central military band that day.
